{"title": "Shepherd of Hermas", "description": "<i>The Shepherd of Hermas</i> is a Christian work likely from the late first half of the second century. It was considered inspired scripture by some of the early Church fathers such as Irenaeus and Origen, but not Tertullian. <i>The Shepherd</i> was very popular amongst Christians in the 2nd and 3rd centuries, and is found in some Bibles after the Acts of the Apostles. The book is made up of five allegorical visions granted to Hermas, a former slave. This is followed by twelve mandates or commandments, and ten similitudes, or parables. (Summary by ancientchristian)", "duration": 14161, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "15807", "name": " Hermas"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/shepherdofhermas_2102_librivox/hermas_2102.jpg", "copyright_year": "1903", "genres": ["Christianity - Other"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "ancientchristian"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "ancientchristian"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "InTheDesert"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Visions 1 & 2", "readers": [14072], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shepherdofhermas_2102_librivox/shepherdofhermas_01_hermas_64kb.mp3", "duration": 895}, {"section": 2, "title": "Vision 3", "readers": [14072], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shepherdofhermas_2102_librivox/shepherdofhermas_02_hermas_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1592}, {"section": 3, "title": "Visions 4 & 5", "readers": [14072], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shepherdofhermas_2102_librivox/shepherdofhermas_03_hermas_64kb.mp3", "duration": 534}, {"section": 4, "title": "The Mandates", "readers": [14072], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shepherdofhermas_2102_librivox/shepherdofhermas_04_hermas_64kb.mp3", "duration": 3218}, {"section": 5, "title": "Similitudes 1 - 5", "readers": [14072], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shepherdofhermas_2102_librivox/she